title: For Sale:  Very Rare Krag Jorgensen -- Norwegian 6.5x55 -- Stomperud Krag --
postcontent:
For sale is a very rare Krag Jorgensen rifle. This Krag is one of the hard to find Norwegian Stomperud models in 6.5x55 Caliber. These rifles were MFG 1946-1951 and this is one out of 1572 pieces that Kongsberg made. They were assembled from different types of parts and rifles given to Kongsberg. They were called "Bastard-Krag" or "Stomperud" Krag. These are a part of the Norwegian Krag history, and this a great sample out of these. Low number of them, so a bit rare to find complete. These were civilian rifles with bayonet lugs to be sold to the public. The Stomperud Krag had the barrel shortened by 15 cm to 61.3 cm and the front of the stock was cut sum 18 cm shorter. This rifle is about the same length as a K98. These rifles are rather scarce with less than 1600 manufactured. The condition of this gun is very good. The serial number on the receiver is #85XXX and the date is stamped 1909. The receiver number revealed that in April 1940 it was an original m1894 Krag, stationarized at the IR3 (Infantry Regiment number 3). IR3 fought against the Germans for a few days, and this Krag can be one that were out in action and perhaps got some damage, so that it later were refurbished as a Stomperud? This is only speculation, but could be the history of the Receiver. The rifle is in very good shape with strong rifling and a clean bore. The only things that make this an excellent rifle rather than perfect is that is my grandfather varnished the stock back in the 60's and my dad wrote Norway on it about an inch long with an electric pencil in the mid 70's. ARMSLIST would only allow 3 pictures. I will email more pictures upon request

One just sold on Gun Broker for $3526. I would put it up auction but, I’m looking for a quick sale. Only $2,850 or Best Offer.

I am not an expert on Krag rifles so please ask any questions you may have. Call or text 480-331-732five

The AWC Amphibian S is an integrally suppressed 22 LR small caliber semi-automatic pistol. This exceptionally quiet pistol is made up of two parts: the Ruger Mk. III .22 LR pistol, and the lightweight custom Titanium AWC suppressor, combined together in a striking fashion. The result is an extremely accurate, lightweight weapon.

This Amphibian S comes equipped with high-visibility adjustable night sights, a frame-mounted American-style magazine release and a loaded chamber indicator. The 7” overall length makes for easy handling and transport, and the durable stainless finish ensures that the Amphibian S will handle a lot of wear and any climate and terrain.

The Ruger Mk. III is equipped with a loaded chamber indicator, which will always let you know when a cartridge is in the chamber. The gun also includes a manual safety, and the internal cylindrical bolt ensures permanent alignment and higher accuracy potential than typical moving slide designs.

The Amphibian S is much lighter than any of the previous variations because of AWC’s new baffle design; the new baffle utilizes a 303 stainless steel primary baffle and a lightweight Titanium secondary baffle.

Ruger also includes Weaver rails as a standard upgrade for connecting sights and other accessories. This suppressed semi-auto is so quiet, the sound of the bullet hitting the dirt was louder than the report. It’s a great addition to your handgun collection, or an ideal buy if you’re looking for a suppressed pistol.
